# Travel System Requirements

## System Overview

The system manages employee travel missions from request creation until financial settlement and closure.

Mission Types: National, International.

The system automates approvals, travel cost calculation, payment processing, mission closure, and financial settlement.

## Workflow

Assigned Person creates mission request.

Line Manager approves.

Division Manager approves.

Travel Team reviews and enters travel costs.

Treasury processes payment.

Mission becomes active.

Mission may be extended if required.

Assigned Person closes mission.

Finance performs settlement.

Mission is completed.

## User Roles

Assigned Person

Line Manager

Division Manager

Travel Team

Treasury

Finance

HR

## Mission Statuses

Draft

Pending Line Manager Approval

Pending Division Manager Approval

Pending Travel Review

Pending Payment

Mission Active

Mission Extended

Mission Closed

Pending Settlement

Completed

Rejected

## Business Controls

Employee cannot have more than one open mission.

National and International missions are supported.

National missions use local currency.

International missions use foreign currency.

Destination list is configurable.

Mission extension is supported.

Long-term missions are handled as separate monthly missions.

